unit.name: 9 Panzer Div HQ
unit.History: The 9th Panzer Division was formed in 1940 from the 4th Light Division, which in turn was formed from the Fast Division of the former Austrian Bundesheer.The division took part in the campaign in the West, first in the Netherlands and later in France. It fought in Yugoslavia before being committed on the Eastern front, first in the central and then in the southern section. In April 1944 it was send to France for rest and re-equipment. It fought in France and Belgium, and in October 1944 launched a counterattack in the Netherlands against the US 7th Armored Division. At the start of operation "Wacht am Rhein" the division was held in reserve, and earmarked for an attack in the Venlo sector with the 15th Army. When this attack was cancelled, the division was sent to the 5th Panzer Army.

commander.Name: Harald Freiherr von Elverfeld
commander.PersBio: Elverfeld served as a staff officer in the staff of the 3rd Light Division, the XIV and LVI Panzerkorps and the 9th and 17th Army. On September 16, 1944 he took over command of the 9th Panzer Division, which he led with distinction, earning the Knight's Cross in December 1944.
